{"lemma":"مُسْلِمُو","slug":"مُسْلِمُو","root":"س.ل.م","root_slug":"س-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُسْلِم","root":"سلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":39},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20559"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%84%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Muslim"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Muslim"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"submitting, accepting, believing.","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تُجَادِلُوا أَهْلَ الْكِتَابِ إِلَّا بِٱلَّتِي هِيَ أَحْسَنُ إِلَّا الَّذِينَ ظَلَمُوا مِنْهُمْ وَقُولُوا آمَنَّا بِالَّذِي أُنْزِلَ إِلَيْنَا وَأُنْزِلَ إِلَيْكُمْ وَإِلَهُنَا وَإِلَهُكُمْ وَاحِدٌ وَنَحْنُ لَهُ مُسْلِمُونَ","english":"Mufti Taqi: Do not debate with the people of the Book unless it is in the best manner, except with those of them who commit injustice. And say, “We believe in what is sent down to us and sent down to you, and our God and your God is One, and to Him we submit (ourselves).”"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unimpaired, intact, unblemished, flawless"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"accepted, uncontested, incontestable, indisputable, incontrovertible"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of أَسْلَمَ (ʔaslama, “to surrender, to become a Muslim”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of سَلَّمَ (sallama, “to preserve, to hand over intact, to accept”)."},"ipa":["/mus.lim/","/mu.sal.lam/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20559","headword_ar":"مُسْلِمٌ","root":"slm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of 4 [q. v.]. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@joEalonaA","text_ar":"وَا@جْعَلْنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimiyna laka","text_ar":"مُسْلِمِينَ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur ii. 122, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make both of us self-resigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, to Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sincere in religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without hypocrisy, towards Thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxoliSayoni","text_ar":"مُخْلِصَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Bd:) and therefore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mslmyn","text_ar":"مسلمين"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  [It commonly means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who holds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"professes, the religion of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAm","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^ana kaAfirFA vum~a huwaAlyawoma musolamapN","text_ar":"كَاَنَ كَافِرًا ثُمَّ هُوَاليَوْمَ مُسْلَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was an unbeliever: then, to day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"he has become"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a Muslim"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["Bd","Jel","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}